<TITLE> Parliament mourns Nimtali, Begunbari victims </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 6 (bdnews24.com)--The parliament on Sunday mourned the dead in the Old Dhaka fire and Begunbari building collapse. Speaker Abdul Hamid placed the obituary reference at the start of the session. The assembly started at 4:10pm without the attendance of main opposition BNP. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina, deputy parliament leader Syeda Sajeda Chowdhury and other MPs were present. At least 117 people were killed in the deadliest fire at Nimtali on the night of June 3 and 25 people died after a five-storey building toppled off its base at Begunbari on June 1. The speaker expressed sympathy for the bereaved families. One-minute silence was observed in parliament in respect for the dead and a special prayer was offered. Awami League MP Matiur Rahman administered the prayer. A national day of mourning was observed on Saturday for those who died in the Nimatli fire. National flags were kept at half-mast at all government offices. 
